SIMPLE: daft
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Daft
<hw>Daft</hw> <pr>(d⟦adot⟧ft)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>daft</ets>, <ets>deft</ets>, <ets>deft</ets>, stupid; prob. the
same word as E. <ets>deft</ets>. See <er>Deft</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Stupid; foolish; idiotic; also, delirious; insane; <as>as, he has
gone <ex>daft</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Let us think no more of this <qex>daft</qex> business</q>
<rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Gay; playful; frolicsome.</def> <mark>[Scot.]</mark>
<rj><au>Jamieson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Daftness</ent>⟦br⟧
